website_summaries.verdict: Uses a proprietary formula to create a cat food that's high in natural protein concentration, but it's pricey per ounce.
pros: Primary ingredients include muscle, organs, and ground-up bone to deliver protein and calcium
Works equally well as treats or as cat food
Easy to soften the texture by soaking the food in water for several minutes
cons: Makes use of some vegetables and plants, meaning it's not quite as protein-rich as some others

customer_reviews.title: It's fabulous, my 20. 3 lb Black Boo ...
customer_reviews.text: It's fabulous, my 20.3 lb Black Boo Boo, loves it. He and I wish I could feed it twice a day but it's too expensive for my budget. So he is fed 1/4 cup every morning hydrated with 1/4 cup of spring water and 3/4 cup of Vitality in separate bowl for the rest of the day and night. He stands on his hind legs with front feet on the edge of the counter to make sure I am preparing it properly.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: I got a yes from all 4 pets
customer_reviews.text: My 3 cats and picky picky dog love this stuff! I feed it as treats.. I crumble it on top of their canned wet food and I also add water to it to make it sort of like a gravy. They love every version I make it in. One of my cats is 16 with crf (kidney failure) and this is greatly helping him get the protein he needs as it is raw protein and not processed. He is doing very well on if. Wysong is my favorite pet food brand.
customer_reviews.author: cdolphin09

customer_reviews.title: Started a return only to find the seller doesn't accept returns?
customer_reviews.text: This packaged raw, dehydrated dog food came as a bag of loose dried filler. I have not opened the bag, but the description on the side says the company creates nutritious food, not necessarily good looking food. My tiny rescue dog needs bite-sized pieces and has had her teeth removed, so also needs soft food. This would just be glop on a plate and she wouldn't touch it. Why does the seller not take returns of an unopened bag of dry dog food?
customer_reviews.author: Pacific Northwest

customer_reviews.title: So good for cats!
customer_reviews.text: I've been buying the freeze-dried salmon and chicken for my two cats for a few years now and they love it. You may spend a little more up front when buying, but it saves so much money on the back end in terms of vet bills, plus your cats are getting full nutrition and are healthier. Worth the money to say the least, plus they last a long time, especially the salmon. I have both the salmon and chicken in bowls next to their regular food for them to snack on whenever they get the urge. A bowl of the salmon will last almost a month, chicken goes a little more quickly. Two or three bowls per small bag.
customer_reviews.author: Real Herbalist

customer_reviews.title: Wysong Archetype Quail Feline Formula
customer_reviews.text: My four and a half month old kitten absolutely loves the Archetype Quail. He'll eat it right out of the bag but seems to enjoy it even more when I add a few crumbled chunks to his canned formula of Wysong's Epigen Duck. He has had no tummy upsets and/or loose stools and is doing very well on this combination. Should you decide to try the Archetype formula, just make sure you introduce it slowly and in small amounts. By using this as an occasional treat or added in small amounts to your preferred canned cat food, you'll be introducing a safer raw alternative your kitty's diet.
customer_reviews.author: Northwest

customer_reviews.title: Both my cats love it
customer_reviews.text: My two older cats were finicky eaters before we found Wysong. Now they rotate among the canned Epigen diets, with this pollock top-dressing everything. I find that even the canned foods they don't like as much (rabbit, beef) get eaten when this is mixed in. I find that it also helps to add some water to the food for improved consistency. The plastic bucket container is a great improvement over the Archetype bags of quail and rabbit, too, since this reseals much more effectively. Highly recommended.
customer_reviews.author: M. Gondek

customer_reviews.title: Good for cats new to raw food and/or with food sensitivities
customer_reviews.text: My cat was recently diagnosed with IBD and food allergies and while she ignores most raw foods, this one was a hit. The bag we received had a nice mix of ground and clumped food, which made it easy to experiment with different ways of feeding this to her. The winning combo for my cat was to mix some of the ground bits into her wet food. i just wish this came in turkey flavor as we now have to limit her protein intake and can no longer give her chicken.
customer_reviews.author: H. Dileepan

customer_reviews.title: great quality dehydrated raw food - ferrets love it
customer_reviews.text: I started buying the Wysong ferret food for our ferrets and they really like it (we alternate with Stella & chewys). I've been giving this one to our ferrets as well and its a big hit. Also our Fox really likes this food as well so we've been giving her this one and the Wysong rabbit formula. I wish it came in larger bags as this little bag does not last us very long.

I'm very happy with this food.

product_meta.description: Flavor Name:Chicken FormulaArchetype is the original raw dog and cat food diet from Wysong and emulates the food canines and felines eat in the wild – the diet they are genetically programmed for.
feature_bullets: Archetype, First And Foremost, Is Not Heated Above 118° Fahrenheit – A True Non-Thermal Freeze-Dried Raw Product!

Starch-Free And Meat-Based, And Thus Does Not Contribute To The Common Carbohydrate Glut Diseases In The Modern Companion Animal Community. Healthy Fats Are Naturally Protected Against Free Radical/Oxidation Degradation. High In Natural Protein And Fat Content
Contains Meats, Plant Nutrients, Nutraceuticals, Prebiotics, Probiotics, Vitamins, Minerals, And An Array Of Micronutrients
Free Of Non-Nutritional Additives Used By Manufacturers To Create Color, Texture, Stool Consistency, Or Shelf-Life. Proven Safe And Nutritious For Well Over A Decade
Wysong Has Been A Leader In Pet Nutrition Since 1979
